Sentencas: Novel NiCo2O4 nanoarrays have been in-situ grown on a La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta(LSM) cathode through a hydrothermal method, which presents the enhanced electrochemical performances of the LSM cathode for the intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: In-situ construction of NiCo2O4 nanoarrays on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ electrodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XRD and SEM have been used to characterize phase structure and morphology of NiCo2O4 nanoarrays.
Titulo: In-situ construction of NiCo2O4 nanoarrays on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ electrodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The LSM cathode, modified by the NiCo2O4 nanoarrays, exhibits excellent electrochemical performances compared with the bare LSM cathode.
Titulo: In-situ construction of NiCo2O4 nanoarrays on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ electrodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum peak power density of single cell, based on the NiCo2O4 nanoarrays modified the LSM cathode, reaches 957 mW cm(-2) at 800 A degrees C, which is almost two times higher than that for the cell based on the bare LSM cathode.
Titulo: In-situ construction of NiCo2O4 nanoarrays on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ electrodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
